{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d0231e67-5978-4db1-bdf6-09cc1b90b6b2","content":"Found **1 untestable static call** in your project:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n\nThis is hard to test because you can't control the return value in unit tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `timezone.now()` with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or Python's `unittest.mock.patch`, or inject the clock as a dependency:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests you can use `freezegun` or `mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now')` to pin the time.\n\nThis is a small project with only one occurrence — easy to fix now before it spreads!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa580f46-5724-404f-8222-6a3f82b6645c","outputTokens":203,"requestId":"9820:24F978:13689A1:1850EE3:69FFF414"},"id":"48ec9389-5fb8-4785-908c-07e0af2512c0","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:57:31.332Z","parentId":"c96979a9-01dd-400e-ba5a-7a78563bf91c"}
